      "options": {
        "content": "## Known Benign Events\n\n### ‚úÖ PostgreSQL Health Checks\n- **Rule**: \"Read sensitive file untrusted\"\n- **Process**: `pg_isready`\n- **Reason**: Postgres healthcheck reads `/etc/shadow` (normal behavior)\n- **Action**: None required - this is expected\n\n### ‚úÖ Container Startup Events\n- **Rule**: \"Terminal shell in container\"\n- **Reason**: Some containers spawn shells during initialization\n- **Action**: Review logs if persists after startup (>5 minutes)\n\n### ‚úÖ Package Manager Operations\n- **Rule**: \"Write below etc\"\n- **Process**: `apt`, `apk`, `yum`, `dnf`\n- **Reason**: Normal package installation/update operations\n- **Action**: Verify operation was intentional\n\n---\n\n## ‚ö†Ô∏è Investigate These Events\n\n### üî¥ High Priority - Investigate Immediately\n- **Unexpected network connections** to unknown IPs\n- **File modifications** in `/etc`, `/bin`, `/usr/bin`, `/lib`\n- **Privilege escalation** attempts (sudo, su without authorization)\n- **Unknown processes** spawning in containers\n- **Reverse shells** or interactive shells in production containers\n- **Sensitive file reads** by unexpected processes\n\n### üü° Medium Priority - Review Within 24h\n- **Write operations** to system directories during non-maintenance windows\n- **New listening ports** opened by containers\n- **Changes to cron jobs** or systemd services\n- **Package installations** outside of planned updates\n\n### üîµ Low Priority - Review When Convenient\n- **DNS lookups** to unusual domains (check if part of app functionality)\n- **Repeated failed login attempts** (might be normal if from fail2ban testing)\n- **File access** to configuration files (verify if part of normal operation)\n\n---\n\n## Investigation Steps\n\n1. **Check container logs**:\n   ```bash\n   docker logs <container-name> --tail 100\n   ```\n\n2. **Check process list**:\n   ```bash\n   docker top <container-name>\n   ```\n\n3. **Review recent changes**:\n   ```bash\n   docker exec <container-name> ls -lat /etc | head -20\n   ```\n\n4. **Check network connections**:\n   ```bash\n   docker exec <container-name> netstat -tuln\n   ```\n\n5. **Review authentication logs** (if applicable):\n   ```bash\n   docker exec <container-name> tail -50 /var/log/auth.log\n   ```\n\n**See SECURITY_OPS_GUIDE.md for detailed incident response procedures.**",
        "mode": "markdown"
